-- Brent Oil Gains 1% in London, Reversing Yesterday’s Fall
-- B y   J o h n   B u c k l e y
-- 2012-07-05T08:40:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-05/brent-oil-gains-1-in-london-reversing-yesterday-s-fall.html
Brent crude rose as much as 1 percent
in  London  following yesterday’s 0.9 percent drop.  Brent for August settlement gained as much as $1.01 to
$100.78 a barrel and traded at $100.68 at 9:40 a.m. on the ICE
Futures Europe exchange in London.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Buckley at 
